A graphical image: png, jpeg, etc.  Stored in mongo as an object containing properties for metadata ('name', 'type'), and base64-encoded binary data ('data', 'thumbData').  

The format of the binary data is in fact a proper "data URL" ({@link https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/Data_URIs}) that can be rendered in the browser by placing in an html <img> tag's src attribute.

